&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Senior Medical Secretary Band 4 | Audio Typing and Secretarial Administration | Bristol | Full Time and Permanent -Monday to Friday.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Spire Bristol Hospital have an exciting opportunity for a Senior Secretary ready for their next challenge, to join our team to support our Consultants in providing a high quality service, on a full time and permanent basis. Working with and leading our wonderful team, you will be pivotal in ensuring an effective and efficient service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Long established since 1987, Spire Bristol Hospital have been providing excellent care, expertise and knowledge in a safe, clean environment for over 25 years, offering the greatest range of high quality treatments, services and diagnostic facilities in the South West.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Duties and responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leading the team in the provision of an efficient and timely secretarial service to assigned consultants and any other associated teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Production of medical letters, operation/clinic notes and discharge summaries&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Developing strong working relationships with our Consultants, Administration Teams, Nursing staff and a range of other departments and patients.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we&#39;re looking for:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To be considered for the role, we would ideally like to see applications from established Medical Secretaries with experience of healthcare and knowledge of medical terminology - this can be one specialism&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong audio-typing and administration skills are essential&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Previous team management and/or leadership skills is also a requirement for this role.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We offer employees a competitive salary as well as a comprehensive benefits package which includes but is not limited to:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;35 days annual leave inclusive of bank holidays&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Employer and employee contributory pension with flexible retirement options&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;‘Spire for you’ reward platform - discount and cashback for over 1000 retailers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Free Bupa wellness screening&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Private medical insurance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Life assurance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We commit to our employees well-being through work life balance, on-going development, support and reward.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Spire Healthcare is a leading independent hospital group that has been putting patients at the heart of everything we do for over 40 years. We have 39 hospitals, 10 clinics and a Specialist Cancer Care Centre across England, Wales and Scotland.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;For us, it&#39;s more than just treating patients; it&#39;s about looking after people.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Closing date: In order to streamline our recruitment process, we reserve the right to expire vacancies prior to the advertised closing date once we have received a sufficient number of applications&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
